Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.12,0:52:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,I think the religion of the IVC is Proto -Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.36,0:52:48.04,English,,0,0,0,,And the reason why is,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.34,0:52:50.80,English,,0,0,0,,if you look at Zoroastrianism,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.82,0:52:54.50,English,,0,0,0,,and you look at Proto -Indo -Iranian,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.52,0:52:57.18,English,,0,0,0,,the religion, there are a lot of similarities. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.42,0:53:03.38,English,,0,0,0,,And Proto -Zoroastrianism actually fits into the larger Proto -Indo -European religion framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.38,0:53:05.38,English,,0,0,0,,When you look at Hinduism,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.42,0:53:08.26,English,,0,0,0,,you've got this strange idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.52,0:53:11.70,English,,0,0,0,,a belief in karma, dharma,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.90,0:53:14.74,English,,0,0,0,,reincarnation, impermanence,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.84,0:53:16.74,English,,0,0,0,,Brahma, the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.22,0:53:23.08,English,,0,0,0,,Like this is not part of the Proto -Indo -European religion in anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.52,0:53:28.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So at the same time, Hinduism,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.78,0:53:30.90,English,,0,0,0,,Buddhism, Jainism, and
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.90,0:53:35.34,English,,0,0,0,,Shikism all share this fundamental belief in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.34,0:53:39.04,English,,0,0,0,,that this world is a false reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.46,0:53:42.38,English,,0,0,0,,It's a reality created by our false beliefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.02,0:53:45.62,English,,0,0,0,,And if we learn to tame our emotions,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.84,0:53:48.10,English,,0,0,0,,if we learn to see the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.10,0:53:51.92,English,,0,0,0,,underlying reality governing all human structure,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.18,0:53:53.98,English,,0,0,0,,then we will be released from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.12,0:53:56.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Now, where would that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.32,0:53:59.72,English,,0,0,0,,That must have come from the IVC because there would be no other place.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.42,0:54:03.28,English,,0,0,0,,Also, it explains why these religions,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.36,0:54:05.80,English,,0,0,0,,have such huge followings in India, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.94,0:54:08.88,English,,0,0,0,,They don't have any followings anywhere else. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.72,0:54:14.46,English,,0,0,0,,Like Hinduism is basically localized to India.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.70,0:54:17.38,English,,0,0,0,,So is Jainism, so is Shikism. So
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.38,0:54:22.90,English,,0,0,0,,they are appealing to a fundamental sense of the world among Indians.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.30,0:54:26.42,English,,0,0,0,,They're basically appealing to nostalgia. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.52,0:54:28.50,English,,0,0,0,,And where is this nostalgia from?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.74,0:54:30.28,English,,0,0,0,,It must be from the IVC.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.20,0:54:32.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So I would make that argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.94,0:54:35.64,English,,0,0,0,,I would make that argument. I would believe, I would bet that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.64,0:54:38.36,English,,0,0,0,,if we're able to construct the religion of the IVC,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.46,0:54:39.38,English,,0,0,0,,the proto -religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.54,0:54:45.02,English,,0,0,0,,we would see a proto -Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.10,0:54:47.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The beginnings of Buddhism. It would be very different.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.68,0:54:50.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because Buddhism evolved over thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.10,0:54:53.54,English,,0,0,0,,But the underlying assumptions about the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.52,0:54:58.08,English,,0,0,0,,basically the idea of oneness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.26,0:55:01.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.84,0:55:02.88,English,,0,0,0,,The idea of false reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.20,0:55:11.40,English,,0,0,0,,I think these two ideas would be very apparent in the IVC.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.50,0:55:14.38,English,,0,0,0,,As they are apparent now in all four major Indian religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.66,0:55:16.68,English,,0,0,0,,Hinduism, Buddhism, Jainism, and Shikism.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.66,0:55:21.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Do you want to continue or?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.32,0:55:24.66,English,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no, no. I'm finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.78,0:55:26.78,English,,0,0,0,,But like do you want to respond to my argument?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.60,0:55:31.68,English,,0,0,0,,No, it's okay. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.10,0:55:34.62,English,,0,0,0,,And I think that's a good argument. Are you guys following along?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.22,0:55:36.38,English,,0,0,0,,Does it make sense to you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.82,0:55:45.30,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, I would argue
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.30,0:55:46.82,English,,0,0,0,,that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.82,0:55:52.18,English,,0,0,0,,we as humans fundamentally have a nostalgia for these two ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.62,0:55:54.96,English,,0,0,0,,Oneness and false reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.34,0:55:58.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because if you look at the West, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.26,0:56:01.52,English,,0,0,0,,If you look at us today, there are two ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.98,0:56:05.54,English,,0,0,0,,The most powerful today in Western civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.18,0:56:10.84,English,,0,0,0,,The first idea is Plato's Allegory of the Cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.44,0:56:16.14,English,,0,0,0,,Right? The idea that we live in a shadow world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.10,0:56:20.10,English,,0,0,0,,And the truth is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.22,0:56:23.08,English,,0,0,0,,But we have to seek it. It's a very powerful idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.18,0:56:26.04,English,,0,0,0,,Right? And it's very similar, by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.14,0:56:29.76,English,,0,0,0,,to the ideas found in Hinduism and Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.96,0:56:31.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Allegory of the Cave is the first powerful idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.14,0:56:36.36,English,,0,0,0,,And then the second powerful idea is the idea of the Second Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.84,0:56:40.10,English,,0,0,0,,The return of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.88,0:56:42.78,English,,0,0,0,,Because what does the return of Jesus signify?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.98,0:56:45.34,English,,0,0,0,,It signifies paradise on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.72,0:56:48.46,English,,0,0,0,,It signifies the destruction of our current reality
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.46,0:56:51.14,English,,0,0,0,,and the replacement of a new reality
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.14,0:56:53.50,English,,0,0,0,,that creates oneness,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.60,0:56:56.18,English,,0,0,0,,completeness, and wholeness on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.16,0:56:59.58,English,,0,0,0,,So in many ways, I think that's a good argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.38,0:57:04.16,English,,0,0,0,,This is very similar to what
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.16,0:57:08.18,English,,0,0,0,,the Indians are proposing as well. So
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.18,0:57:13.62,English,,0,0,0,,what this is saying is at a fundamental level,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.88,0:57:18.70,English,,0,0,0,,everyone has nostalgia for a distant past.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.30,0:57:21.06,English,,0,0,0,,And what is this distant past?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.44,0:57:23.66,English,,0,0,0,,The distant past is the idea of animism.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.44,0:57:29.02,English,,0,0,0,,So remember, 10,000 years ago, 20,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.58,0:57:31.60,English,,0,0,0,,we were in the Ice Age.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.76,0:57:33.06,English,,0,0,0,,We were hunter -gatherers.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.26,0:57:38.22,English,,0,0,0,,And the way we saw the world was very different from the way we see the world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.80,0:57:41.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Back then, if you were a hunter -gatherer,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.84,0:57:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,you could only think you were the same as the tree or as the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.12,0:57:48.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It's the idea of oneness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.16,0:57:52.46,English,,0,0,0,,We're no different. We're all part of the life cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.80,0:57:56.22,English,,0,0,0,,We're all part of Mother Nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.32,0:57:59.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Mother Goddess. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.46,0:58:03.88,English,,0,0,0,,We also believe we inhabit different realities at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.94,0:58:06.88,English,,0,0,0,,Right? We live in this world, which is the material reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.14,0:58:10.52,English,,0,0,0,,We're also inhabiting the spiritual reality as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.70,0:58:16.08,English,,0,0,0,,And what we do spiritually matters a lot more than what we do materially.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.24,0:58:18.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So we can hunt and
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.18,0:58:22.40,English,,0,0,0,,kill animals as long as we pay the proper respects to the animals we kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.00,0:58:26.44,English,,0,0,0,,As long as we contribute spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.44,0:58:31.00,English,,0,0,0,,We contribute spiritually to the cycle of life
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.00,0:58:32.22,English,,0,0,0,,and death. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.16,0:58:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,So I think that's where Buddhism comes from.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.74,0:58:37.48,English,,0,0,0,,It comes from animism.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.04,0:58:41.94,English,,0,0,0,,This Buddhism became reinforced
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.94,0:58:44.66,English,,0,0,0,,and became much more concrete
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.66,0:58:49.70,English,,0,0,0,,because it was experiencing a reality in Mesopotamia
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.70,0:58:51.52,English,,0,0,0,,and Egypt that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.52,0:58:55.40,English,,0,0,0,,was abhorrent to the people experiencing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.40,0:58:58.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? War goes against the human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.04,0:59:03.00,English,,0,0,0,,Inequality and corruption in ways goes against the human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.14,0:59:07.00,English,,0,0,0,,We fundamentally believe this to be evil and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.34,0:59:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.68,0:59:15.52,English,,0,0,0,,is my argument about the IBC.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.06,0:59:17.08,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.92,0:59:30.28,English,,0,0,0,,Any comments?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.50,0:59:34.30,English,,0,0,0,,You seem to believe that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.30,0:59:37.56,English,,0,0,0,,human beings are incredibly benevolent
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.56,0:59:41.98,English,,0,0,0,,and kind until they're back to the state they've been trained to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.34,0:59:44.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. That's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.02,0:59:48.82,English,,0,0,0,,Do I believe that human nature is fundamentally benevolent?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.12,0:59:52.94,English,,0,0,0,,I don't believe human nature is benevolent.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.94,0:59:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,I believe humans naturally seek
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.16,0:59:59.68,English,,0,0,0,,a spiritual understanding of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.28,1:00:02.58,English,,0,0,0,,I think humans want to know why.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.78,1:00:05.54,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we here? Where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.60,1:00:08.92,English,,0,0,0,,Where do we come from? Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.00,1:00:12.78,English,,0,0,0,,We want to know why. We're also curious.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.16,1:00:14.50,English,,0,0,0,,We want to explore the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.72,1:00:17.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So I think trade is not a new invention.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.60,1:00:21.58,English,,0,0,0,,I think it's a very inherent thing to human nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.58,1:00:23.38,English,,0,0,0,,I think the idea of globalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.94,1:00:26.00,English,,0,0,0,,This was a globalized world like 5,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.18,1:00:29.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Extremely sophisticated, complex, globalized world.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.60,1:00:33.48,English,,0,0,0,,So I think that's what makes us fundamentally human.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.08,1:00:37.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And you can say this is a good thing or a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.44,1:00:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,And I would say, well, it depends on the circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.04,1:00:45.08,English,,0,0,0,,Right? But I think what drives us as humans is our curiosity
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.08,1:00:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.04,1:00:50.58,English,,0,0,0,,our imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.32,1:00:53.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's what I think being human is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.12,1:00:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,And sometimes this is a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.04,1:00:57.44,English,,0,0,0,,Sometimes this is a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.54,1:01:03.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Sometimes in the IVC this will lead to peace
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.18,1:01:05.00,English,,0,0,0,,and egalitarianism. But
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.00,1:01:09.16,English,,0,0,0,,this also is what drives the idea of the second coming,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.36,1:01:12.48,English,,0,0,0,,which is what's driving the conflict in the Middle East today.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.30,1:01:15.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So it depends on the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.22,1:01:17.86,English,,0,0,0,,It depends on the circumstance. If this curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.00,1:01:21.52,English,,0,0,0,,this imagination is channeled effectively, then the idea of the second coming then I think that's a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.92,1:01:26.36,English,,0,0,0,,If it's channeled opportunistically, then it's a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.36,1:01:31.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Okay, but thanks for the question. Any more questions?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.80,1:01:43.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So this ends our Bronze Age unit.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.72,1:01:46.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So we looked at the three major Bronze Age civilizations,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.62,1:01:49.56,English,,0,0,0,,Egypt, Mesopotamia, and IVC.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.44,1:01:53.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Next class we'll start the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.96,1:01:56.60,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Hebrew Bible. All right.
